President Trump met with the leaders of the Los Angeles 2028 Olympic Committee at the Montage Beverly Hills. He praised their work in bringing the Olympics to Los Angeles and mentioned that he made a call to the Olympic Committee when he was President-elect, as the previous administration had refused to call them. He signed a document pledging the federal government's support for the 2028 Olympics and emphasized the economic benefits it will bring, including job creation and economic growth. The President also discussed the importance of ensuring the safety and security of the games and mentioned the federal government's role in addressing the homeless situation in Los Angeles. He expressed confidence in Team USA's performance and stated his willingness to attend the Olympics in Tokyo this summer if possible. The President also criticized sanctuary cities and stated his intention to take action if they don't address the issue. Overall, the meeting focused on the support and preparations for the upcoming 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles.